Hello?

05:41.372 --> 05:45.975
What do you mean have
I checked the children?

05:46.044 --> 05:47.577
Seriously, stop.

05:47.645 --> 05:50.746
Did you just say the calls
are coming from...

05:50.815 --> 05:52.765
inside the house?

05:53.337 --> 05:58.173
Ah!

06:01.092 --> 06:02.792
That doesn't even make sense.

06:02.861 --> 06:04.260
So the scary guy that was calling

06:04.329 --> 06:06.596
just told you he was
calling from inside the house?

06:06.664 --> 06:09.296
We've practically missed
the whole movie because of you.

06:09.321 --> 06:10.466
Well, you're not missing much.

06:10.535 --> 06:12.268
Billy Bob and the killer
decapitate each other

06:12.337 --> 06:14.170
at the exact same time at the end.

06:14.239 --> 06:17.188
- Ugh.
- Are you kidding me?

06:19.571 --> 06:20.904
I'll go now.

06:24.182 --> 06:26.816
- Your mom sucks.
- She's not my mom.

06:26.885 --> 06:29.485
She's just some lady my dad likes.

06:36.657 --> 06:39.024
Blake's really excited
to go camping this weekend.

06:39.092 --> 06:41.500
He's been collecting spiders
all week to throw in the fire.

06:41.525 --> 06:42.719
Mm-hmm.

06:43.664 --> 06:45.047
Is everything okay?

06:46.433 --> 06:48.313
I don't think Blake likes me.

06:48.852 --> 06:50.602
Is this because of his
reaction when I told him

06:50.671 --> 06:53.657
that you were my girlfriend?
Don't take that personally.

06:53.682 --> 06:55.140
He can't emote while he's eating.

06:55.208 --> 06:57.475
No, it's more than that.

06:57.544 --> 07:00.766
Last night I tried bonding with
him, but he wasn't interested.

07:01.348 --> 07:03.048
I just don't know how this is gonna work

07:03.116 --> 07:04.883
if your son doesn't like me.

07:04.951 --> 07:08.887
Oh, no, this is over, isn't it?
You're gonna break up with me.

07:08.955 --> 07:10.755
Oh, no, I can't believe it's over.

07:10.824 --> 07:12.657
Whoa, calm down.

07:12.726 --> 07:14.259
I am not breaking up with you.

07:14.328 --> 07:16.618
Blake just needs to get
to know you better.

07:17.993 --> 07:19.597
Why don't you come with us this weekend?

07:19.666 --> 07:21.700
Camping? I don't know.

07:21.768 --> 07:23.301
I've never really been before.

07:23.370 --> 07:26.404
- What about Rapture Camp?
- That's not really camping.

07:26.473 --> 07:28.473
We just leave behind all of
our earthly possessions

07:28.542 --> 07:29.874
and wait in the woods.

07:29.943 --> 07:32.143
Well, this is gonna be
a little bit different.

07:32.212 --> 07:34.746
- Okay. Do I need a gun?
- No.

07:34.815 --> 07:36.047
- For snakes?
- Nope.

07:36.116 --> 07:37.482
Okay, I guess if I see a snake,

07:37.551 --> 07:39.071
I'll just bash it
over the head with a rock.

07:41.126 --> 07:45.229
"Li Min sat alone in the
corner of her damp, dank cell.

07:45.321 --> 07:48.256
"Was she truly alive if she
couldn't go where she wanted,

07:48.324 --> 07:50.391
"communicate with people she loved?

07:50.460 --> 07:52.326
"She found herself praying for death,

07:52.395 --> 07:55.129
"a sweet release from
her meaningless life."

07:57.672 --> 07:59.700
- Chelsea, wake up.
- Oh.

07:59.769 --> 08:01.569
- What?
- You fell asleep.

08:01.638 --> 08:04.790
I'm sorry, but your reading
is putting me into a coma.

08:04.961 --> 08:07.074
Do you wanna read the next chapter?

08:07.143 --> 08:09.176
This lady doesn't even know we're here.

08:09.374 --> 08:10.507
What's the point of giving back

08:10.532 --> 08:11.846
if they can't even say "thank you"?

08:11.914 --> 08:12.947
She can hear us.

08:13.016 --> 08:14.115
We should be doing something

08:14.183 --> 08:15.883
that will actually help these people.

08:18.655 --> 08:20.407
There you go...

08:21.024 --> 08:24.292
Janice. You look beautiful.

08:24.360 --> 08:26.961
- What're you doing?
- Giving Janice a makeover.

08:27.030 --> 08:28.329
Why would anyone wanna wake up

08:28.398 --> 08:29.897
when they look like a cold, dead fish.

08:29.966 --> 08:32.789
Now she looks beautiful and fierce.

08:33.243 --> 08:34.750
Isn't that right, Janice?

08:36.839 --> 08:38.873
See? She likes it.

08:40.243 --> 08:41.890
Give me a smile, Deb.

08:42.879 --> 08:45.680
Now, Deb, think about the hot dog.

08:45.748 --> 08:48.616
- What?
- The genuine Chicago dog.

08:48.685 --> 08:51.285
- Think about it.
- You can smell the hot dog.

08:51.354 --> 08:54.055
- Mm-hmm.
- It smells like summer,

08:54.123 --> 08:56.891
like childhood, like America.

08:56.959 --> 08:59.894
And this makes you proud. Be proud, Deb.

09:02.612 --> 09:04.071
That's your proud?

09:05.134 --> 09:08.079
- She's not delivering.
- I know. Okay.

09:08.774 --> 09:09.904
Forget pride.

09:09.972 --> 09:13.240
Uh, you're a fiery Chicago broad

09:13.508 --> 09:15.943
who curses every third word.

09:16.012 --> 09:17.278
That's it, yes.

09:17.347 --> 09:18.779
And all you want is that hot dog,

09:18.848 --> 09:20.281
so you gotta go out
and get that hot dog.

09:20.350 --> 09:21.916
Look at the dog. Look at the dog.

09:21.984 --> 09:23.918
- Yeah.
- Look at the dog.

09:23.943 --> 09:24.996
Look at the dog.

09:30.026 --> 09:31.457
That's really nice, hon,

09:31.482 --> 09:33.294
but I don't think we'll use it.

09:33.363 --> 09:35.425
Yeah, there's not even a river.

09:36.894 --> 09:38.999
Oh, well, I blew it up anyway.

09:39.068 --> 09:40.222
Just in case.

09:41.339 --> 09:44.271
Oh! And I brought this
water filtration bottle

09:44.340 --> 09:46.807
that can recycle urine
into potable water.

09:46.876 --> 09:48.743
I could go now and in ten minutes

09:48.811 --> 09:50.128
we could all have a glass.

09:50.647 --> 09:52.247
Oh, we have drinking water.

09:52.448 --> 09:55.149
Why don't you and Blake
go gather some sticks

09:55.218 --> 09:56.596
while I finish pitching the tent?

09:56.621 --> 09:59.320
Okay. Come on, partner.

09:59.389 --> 10:01.288
Why are you talking like a cowboy?

10:01.357 --> 10:04.258
I have no idea. Now, giddy up.

10:04.480 --> 10:05.926
I'm sorry.

10:05.995 --> 10:08.714
Dagnabbit... ah, I did it again.

10:14.103 --> 10:15.925
It's all about the volume, Irma.

10:16.539 --> 10:19.006
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

10:19.075 --> 10:20.902
Nurse, help.

10:21.911 --> 10:23.144
Thank God you're here.

10:23.212 --> 10:25.579
I can't leave her with half a blowout.

10:32.789 --> 10:34.054
What're you doing?

10:34.123 --> 10:35.746
Throwing away the tree garbage.

10:36.222 --> 10:37.816
The sticks are for the fire.

10:38.238 --> 10:41.028
Oh, right.

10:41.097 --> 10:43.164
Do you see that? It's a barn owl.

10:43.232 --> 10:45.366
- What?
- A barn owl.

10:45.435 --> 10:47.134
Oh, I can't believe
I'm seeing one in person.

10:47.203 --> 10:48.469
And she's a female.

10:48.538 --> 10:50.070
You can tell by her spotted chest.

10:50.139 --> 10:52.840
Wow, she's beautiful.

10:52.909 --> 10:54.375
Did you know barn owls don't hoot?

10:54.444 --> 10:57.077
They screech, like this,.

10:57.146 --> 10:58.546
How do you know so much about them?

