11:00.082 --> 11:02.136
after my mom got a job at Hooters.

11:03.686 --> 11:05.085
You know what animal I love?

11:05.154 --> 11:06.855
The black-bellied whistling duck.

11:07.011 --> 11:08.889
I think it's really funny
a duck can whistle.

11:08.958 --> 11:10.124
Yeah, those are cool.

11:10.193 --> 11:11.492
You know what other animal I like?

11:11.561 --> 11:14.161
Tortoises. They can live to be over 100.

11:14.230 --> 11:15.896
One time at the zoo,
I saw two of them humping.

11:15.965 --> 11:17.331
And no one stopped me,

11:17.400 --> 11:18.866
so I just stood
and watched them forever.

11:26.652 --> 11:28.542
Caroline, I see another nose hair.

11:28.611 --> 11:30.511
- It's really pulling focus.
- Well, I know.

11:30.580 --> 11:32.379
But every time I pluck one,
another one sprouts up.

11:32.448 --> 11:34.448
- Okay, we're done.
- Oh.

11:34.517 --> 11:36.217
I'm tired, sweaty, and my baby

11:36.285 --> 11:38.052
is tap dancing on my bladder.

11:38.120 --> 11:40.454
But we haven't even gotten
to the Navy Pier shot.

11:40.523 --> 11:42.316
- No, give me the camera.
- Oh.

11:45.332 --> 11:49.196
Damn, I am one beautiful bitch.

11:49.265 --> 11:51.509
Told you. Toby's amazing.

11:51.534 --> 11:52.900
Oh.

11:52.925 --> 11:56.237
Okay, well, I guess we can keep going.

11:56.949 --> 11:59.240
Caroline, more hairspray.

11:59.308 --> 12:01.519
You missed some fly-aways
in some of those shots.

12:01.566 --> 12:04.712
Pump up the lip gloss,
and where is the lint roller?

12:04.780 --> 12:07.848
I'm not a carpet, people.
I shouldn't look like one.

12:09.785 --> 12:11.619
So, how's everything going with Blake?

12:11.687 --> 12:14.889
Actually, really well.
We saw a barn owl.

12:14.957 --> 12:17.424
Oh, sounds like a hoot.

12:17.493 --> 12:18.996
My famous chili's ready.

12:19.808 --> 12:22.429
Oh, I'm afraid I'll have to pass.

12:22.498 --> 12:24.417
I don't do too well with chili.

12:26.136 --> 12:27.301
Fine.

12:27.370 --> 12:28.936
I don't know why I carried
chili for three

12:29.005 --> 12:30.472
in my backpack all day.

12:32.355 --> 12:34.746
You know what? I'd love some.

12:40.449 --> 12:43.253
Mmm. This is good.

12:43.519 --> 12:45.185
This is really good. Who are you?

12:45.254 --> 12:46.987
Emeril Lagasse? Bam!

12:47.056 --> 12:48.589
Paula Deen? Add some butter.

12:48.658 --> 12:50.991
Guy Fieri? Flavortown, population: me.

12:51.060 --> 12:52.167
Ah.

12:53.796 --> 12:55.128
Mmm.

12:55.496 --> 12:57.363
Can I have another bowl?

12:57.770 --> 12:59.792
Whoa. Okay.

13:08.852 --> 13:12.347
Okay, ready? One, two, three.

13:14.617 --> 13:17.017
Damn, girl, do they have you
on hair gummies?

13:17.347 --> 13:19.050
This is narsty.

13:22.058 --> 13:23.675
Oh, my God. Dorothy?

13:24.994 --> 13:27.227
Dorothy? She's awake.

13:27.296 --> 13:28.957
Dorothy woke up.

13:30.300 --> 13:32.511
I waxed her out of her coma.

13:36.387 --> 13:38.167
The "Star Wars" movies are the best.

13:38.192 --> 13:39.555
It's so stupid people argue about

13:39.623 --> 13:41.156
whether they're boiler plate stories

13:41.225 --> 13:43.125
following a simple
Joseph Campbell hero template,

13:43.194 --> 13:45.661
or explorations of
the Judeo-Christian motif

13:45.729 --> 13:46.895
of good versus evil.

13:46.964 --> 13:48.897
They're both those things and more.

13:48.966 --> 13:50.999
I'll have to watch them some time.

13:51.174 --> 13:52.440
We can watch them when we get home.

13:52.465 --> 13:54.323
Yeah, we have all nine on Blu-ray.

13:59.443 --> 14:04.279
Mmm, these s'mores are yummy.

14:07.191 --> 14:09.758
He took the girl home,
but when he got out

14:09.826 --> 14:11.660
to open the car door for her...

14:11.728 --> 14:14.761
Uh, what? What happened?

14:15.371 --> 14:18.233
Hanging from the car door handle...

14:18.589 --> 14:22.253
...was a bloody metal hook.

14:23.322 --> 14:25.425
Ah!

14:26.043 --> 14:28.243
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine, I'm fine.

14:28.312 --> 14:29.792
I got scared.

14:41.625 --> 14:43.792
This mile isn't feeling so magnificent.

14:43.817 --> 14:46.051
I'm shiny, I need more powder.

14:46.076 --> 14:47.842
I just powdered you.

14:47.867 --> 14:49.667
I can't even see Flat Bradley.

14:49.692 --> 14:52.230
Can you just rotate
to your left, please?

14:52.255 --> 14:54.322
No. Caroline, get me water.

14:54.504 --> 14:55.683
She's so mean.

14:55.708 --> 14:57.408
I even went out
and bought her that lovely top

14:57.433 --> 14:59.366
and floral-print scarf from JC Penney

14:59.391 --> 15:01.224
and this is how she treats us?

15:01.279 --> 15:02.578
My Spanx are riding up.

15:02.710 --> 15:04.843
Okay, what do you want me to do?

15:04.868 --> 15:06.097
Get in there.

15:09.731 --> 15:10.887
Go deep.

15:13.426 --> 15:15.156
It's really muggy up here.

15:15.225 --> 15:17.692
You know what?
Maybe we can call it a night.

15:17.761 --> 15:20.605
- We've already done 14 setups.
- Fine.

15:21.932 --> 15:25.834
But not until Bradley and I
have our candlelit dinner

15:25.902 --> 15:28.184
at Gibson's Steakhouse.

15:31.074 --> 15:32.809
Flat Bradley.

15:33.000 --> 15:34.166
- Help!
- Oh.

15:34.191 --> 15:36.402
Mm. Let him burn.

15:36.580 --> 15:39.214
Ah... Oh, no.

15:39.283 --> 15:40.644
Oh, God.

15:41.084 --> 15:44.085
We can't thank you enough for
bringing my mother back to us.

15:44.110 --> 15:45.176
It's my pleasure.

15:45.201 --> 15:46.600
I was just looking to give back.

15:46.625 --> 15:48.625
I never thought I'd give back life.

15:48.650 --> 15:51.218
Oh, and FYI, tell Dorothy,
with her small eyes,

15:51.243 --> 15:52.840
she should go easy on the eyeliner.

15:53.175 --> 15:54.207
Okay.

15:54.246 --> 15:57.032
Cecelia, I'm so glad you
brought me here.

15:57.100 --> 15:58.566
I can't promise I'll be able to fix

15:58.635 --> 16:00.068
all the patients tonight, but...

16:00.137 --> 16:01.636
You don't really think you're
responsible

16:01.705 --> 16:02.737
for waking her up, do you?

16:02.806 --> 16:03.957
Listen, Cecelia.

16:04.223 --> 16:06.574
I'm sorry that I'm better
at volunteering than you are.

16:06.643 --> 16:09.379
- It's not a competition.
- Okay, but I did win.

16:09.777 --> 16:11.846
I think if you put more thought
into your work

16:11.871 --> 16:13.204
you'd get better results.

16:13.229 --> 16:14.762
- More thought?
- Yeah.

16:15.252 --> 16:18.320
I spent eight years with
these people, reading to them,

16:18.388 --> 16:20.137
making sure that they know
they're not alone,

16:20.162 --> 16:22.424
trying to give them
a better quality of life.

16:22.492 --> 16:24.793
All you did was show up
and do what was fun for you.

16:24.861 --> 16:26.294
Please do not lecture me.

16:26.363 --> 16:28.596
All you've done is read boring
ass books for years,

16:28.665 --> 16:30.031
and what's the most that's happened?

16:30.100 --> 16:31.366
Someone's farted?

16:31.435 --> 16:33.335
This morning when you came
into the teacher's lounge

16:33.403 --> 16:35.937
talking about the state of the
world and all its injustices,

16:36.006 --> 16:39.240
I thought maybe, just maybe,
she really is changing.

16:39.309 --> 16:41.262
Maybe she really does
wanna make a difference.

16:41.312 --> 16:42.863
But I should've known better.

16:43.465 --> 16:46.132
You've never done a selfless
act in your entire life.

16:46.483 --> 16:48.777
I don't know why I expected
this to be any different.

17:05.402 --> 17:06.605
Oh.

17:10.607 --> 17:11.894
Ah...

17:16.645 --> 17:18.582
Blake. No.

17:22.050 --> 17:23.718
Mm, hmm.

17:23.787 --> 17:25.819
Hey, what's going on?

17:25.888 --> 17:28.390
Dad, I wanna go home. I'm scared.

17:28.458 --> 17:31.326
Is this about the hook?
It's just an urban legend.

17:31.395 --> 17:33.121
I wanna leave. Now.

17:34.139 --> 17:36.652
Okay, buddy. Okay, yeah, we can go.

17:44.174 --> 17:46.176
Dr. McCoy, pick up on line one.

17:46.598 --> 17:48.943
Thanks for taking
a second shift, ladies.

17:49.012 --> 17:53.047
We live to serve so others... can live.

17:53.116 --> 17:54.416
Hmm.

17:54.484 --> 17:57.199
Hi, I'm John Williams with
the "Chicagoland Gazette".

17:57.521 --> 17:59.354
Well, hello there, John Williams.

17:59.423 --> 18:00.989
I'm doing a story on Dorothy Sullivan

18:01.057 --> 18:02.490
coming out of her coma, and
I've been told

18:02.559 --> 18:04.527
that you were with her
when she first woke up.

18:04.552 --> 18:06.085
I would love to get some quotes
for the piece.

18:06.147 --> 18:08.981
Mmm, I would love to give you some.

18:14.237 --> 18:16.777
But the person you should
really talk to is Cecelia.

18:17.874 --> 18:19.441
Cecelia's been by Dorothy's side,

18:19.509 --> 18:21.976
and many of these other
patients' for years.

18:22.045 --> 18:24.668
If you wanna know their story,
you should talk to her.

18:25.282 --> 18:26.981
Are you sure about this, Chelsea?

18:27.050 --> 18:28.383
I know it's your New Year's resolution

18:28.452 --> 18:30.059
- to get your name in print.
- I know,

18:30.084 --> 18:32.053
but I thought about what you
said and you're right.

18:32.122 --> 18:34.422
This isn't about me.
This is about Dorothy.

18:34.491 --> 18:36.891
And I think she would want you
to tell her story.

18:36.960 --> 18:38.359
Plus, girl, it's a great way for you

18:38.428 --> 18:40.637
to get your message out there
about volunteering.

18:41.338 --> 18:43.790
These patients really need more
people like you.

18:43.825 --> 18:45.055
Aw.

18:48.728 --> 18:51.611
- Oh, hi, Blake.
- Mm, my dad's not home.

18:51.775 --> 18:54.053
Actually, I wanted to talk to you.

18:55.057 --> 18:56.523
Okay?

18:56.592 --> 19:00.794
I'm so sorry about everything you saw.

19:01.073 --> 19:03.573
I think it's obvious
why you were scared.

19:03.642 --> 19:05.791
You saw a lot.

19:06.010 --> 19:07.978
And I completely understand

19:08.047 --> 19:10.380
if you never wanna be around me again.

19:10.449 --> 19:12.082
I wasn't scared.

19:12.151 --> 19:14.051
I just figured you'd rather
use the bathroom at home,

19:14.119 --> 19:15.685
so I lied to get us out of there.

19:15.754 --> 19:17.487
I didn't want you to have to tell my dad

19:17.556 --> 19:19.256
you had explosive diarrhea.

19:19.324 --> 19:20.957
Wow, thank you, Blake.

19:21.026 --> 19:23.593
That was incredibly kind of you.

19:23.662 --> 19:25.362
Also, that was a pretty
cool way to poop.

19:25.431 --> 19:27.531
Climbing up on top of
the trash can like that.

19:27.599 --> 19:29.566
That's what raccoons do.

19:29.635 --> 19:31.802
Uh, do me a favor

19:31.870 --> 19:35.471
and don't ever tell anyone you saw that.

19:36.106 --> 19:37.197
Okay?

19:39.745 --> 19:41.617
It's amazing how much you
can learn by giving back

19:41.642 --> 19:43.213
to your community.
When I first started voluntee...

19:43.282 --> 19:44.581
Code blue, code blue.

19:44.650 --> 19:46.349
Some idiot put makeup on Mrs. Gilmore

19:46.418 --> 19:48.919
so nobody noticed she was cyanotic.

19:48.987 --> 19:51.321
When we wiped it off,
she was completely blue.

19:52.991 --> 19:55.658
We gotta get out of here.
Is there a back exit?

19:56.408 --> 19:58.539
Mrs. Gilmore, don't forget your makeup.

